(150, 1, '2015-01-05 13:04:27', '2015-01-05 13:04:27', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Made the Tough Calls and Got Our Fiscal House in Order</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="blue_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n  <div class="inner_blue_container">\r\n    <p class="btm_padding">Mayor Kristen Brown understands she works for the taxpayers who write the checks to local government, not for the special interests who cash the checks. </p>\r\n    <p>Mayor Brown has been shaping city governments organization and budget to lower taxes and fees, best advance your priorities and ensure city government gets the most for your dollar.  This has resulted in changes in the way city government does business and a more streamlined, priority-driven budget. </p>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="img_container"><img src="images/a-record-of-sucess-Fiscal-Responsibility.png"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2>Eliminated Mandatory Fees and Championed a Decrease in Property Taxes</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Repealed the mandatory trash fees from residents utility bills, returning $1.4 million a year to our citizens.</li>\r\n<li>Voted to return $3 million of TIF property tax revenues to the taxpayers to reduce property tax rates.</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2>Changed Spending Priorities</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Terminated the expensive and problematic outdoor sports complex.</li>\r\n<li>nvested in repairing and restoring existing infrastructure, roads and public parks and community facilities, not developing new facilities.</li>\r\n<ul>', 'A Plan for the Future', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '12-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-05 13:04:27', '2015-01-05 13:04:27', '', 12, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/12-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(151, 1, '2015-01-15 10:41:44', '2015-01-15 10:41:44', '<div class="main_heading full_width ">\n<h1 class="red_color ">A Plan for the Future: Advance Columbus</h1>\n<div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="plan_text_container full_width top_margin">\n<div class="inner_blue_container">\n<p class="btm_padding">Our community is a special and remarkable combination of people and place. World-renown architecture is woven into the fabric of our daily lives. We benefit from exciting cultural and recreational amenities, a diverse population, a strong sense of community and teamwork and a commitment to excellence.</p>\nOur local economy is a powerhouse relative to the rest of the state and nation. The number of jobs in our community is at an all-time high. The number of residents employed is also at an all-time high.\n\n</div>\n<div class="plan_rightPart"><a href="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/plan4.png"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/plan4.png" alt="plan" width="438" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-704" /></div>\n</div>\n<div class="plan_inner_part full_width">\n<p class="btm_padding top_margin">By every major measure, our quality of life in Columbus, Indiana is far better than the state and even the nation as a whole.\nBut we are Columbus. We aim even higher and we have an unshakable confidence in our ability to create an even more remarkable future.</p>\n\n<h2 class="red_color btm_padding1">OUR VISION</h2>\n<p class="btm_padding">Our vision is <strong>to be the very best community of its size in the country. </strong> It is a bold and ambitious vision.</p>\n\n<h2 class="blue_color btm_padding1 ">ONE CITY. ONE PLAN. ADVANCE COLUMBUS.</h2>\n<p class="btm_padding1">In order to advance Columbus toward this future, Mayor Kristen Brown partnered with the leaders of several other public and private organizations dedicated to serving our community. Together with much public engagement, they created Advance Columbus, a roadmap to solve our toughest challenges, leverage our greatest strengths and capitalize on our many opportunities to advance our quality of life for today and for future generations.</p>\n<p class="btm_padding1">Mayor Kristen Brown rolled out Advance Columbus at her State of the City address in 2013.</p>\n<p class="btm_padding1">She also made it the City of Columbus mission to do its part in advancing Columbus toward the future we envision. Last year, Mayor Brown and department heads developed the City governments first strategic plan, aligning the city governments priorities with the communitys highest priorities as defined by Advance Columbus.</p>\n<p class="btm_padding1 blue_color_normal">The plans priorities are to:</p>\n<p class="btm_padding1">1. Advance Quality Infrastructure\n\n2. Advance Economic Prosperity and Well-Paying Jobs\n\n3. Advance the Safety and Health of Our Community</p>\n<p class="btm_padding1">Recognizing that how we get there is every bit as important as getting there, Mayor Browns plan importantly includes advancing Columbus in a way that is consistent with the <a>values of good government.</a></p>\n\n</div>', 'A Plan for the Future', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '12-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-01-15 10:41:44', '2015-01-15 10:41:44', '', 12, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/12-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
