(176, 1, '2015-01-06 07:33:29', '2015-01-06 07:33:29', '<div class="main_heading full_width top_margin">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Ushered in a New Era of Good Government </h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin"> \r\n    <p>Mayor Kristen Brown believes that how government operates is every bit as important as what it accomplishes.  Her goal is to be the most honest, transparent, inclusive, responsive and accountable municipal government of our size.  And she and her team are delivering.   </p>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin btm_padding1"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/government1.png" alt="government" width="1001" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-530" /></div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width ">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Dissolved the Citys private corporation, Columbus Downtown Inc., and stopped spending taxpayer money behind closed doors. </li>\r\n<li>Dramatically improved city governments transparency with live and on-demand broadcasting of public meetings online. This service has attracted thousands of views.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Gained adoption of a comprehensive code of ethical conduct, helping assure you that public officials and employees are operating in your best interest  not in their own personal interests or in favor of special interests.  </li>\r\n<li>Attained accreditation for the police department, ensuring our officers maintain the highest professional standards and operate with the utmost integrity, transparency and accountability.  Only three percent of the law enforcement agencies in the nation achieve this status. </li>\r\n<li>Improved service by launching uReport, an online customer service request application that gives you the opportunity to quickly and easily request city services. </li>\r\n<li>Developed a long-term strategic plan for city government with priorities and measurable objectives and published annual reports detailing results.</li>\r\n<li>Achieved a finding-free audit from the Indiana State Board of Accounts in 2013.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Good Government', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'good-government', '', '', '2015-01-14 08:05:19', '2015-01-14 08:05:19', '', 10, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/?page_id=176', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(177, 1, '2015-01-06 07:33:29', '2015-01-06 07:33:29', '', 'Good Government', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '176-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-06 07:33:29', '2015-01-06 07:33:29', '', 176, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/176-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(178, 1, '2015-01-06 07:33:41', '2015-01-06 07:33:41', '<div class="main_heading full_width top_margin">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Made Tough Calls to Get Our Fiscal House in Order and Lower Taxes </h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n    <p class="btm_padding">Mayor Kristen Brown understands she works for the taxpayers who write the checks to local government, not for the special interests who cash the checks. </p>\r\n    <p >Mayor Brown has been shaping city governments organization and budget to lower taxes and fees, best advance your priorities and ensure city government gets the most for your dollar.  This has resulted in changes in the way city government does business and a more streamlined, priority-driven budget. </p>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/about_img3.png" alt="about_img3" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-602" /></div>\r\n\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n<h2>Eliminated Mandatory Fees and Championed a Decrease in Property Taxes</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Repealed the mandatory trash fees from residents utility bills, returning $1.4 million a year to our citizens.</li>\r\n<li>Voted to return $3 million of TIF property tax revenues to the taxpayers to reduce property tax rates.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2>Changed Spending Priorities</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Terminated the expensive and problematic outdoor sports complex.</li>\r\n<li>Invested in repairing and restoring existing infrastructure, roads and public parks and community facilities, not developing new facilities.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2>Saved Taxpayers Money</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Conducted competitive purchasing processes for services and consolidated purchasing of supplies and equipment, saving taxpayers more than a million dollars a year.  </li>\r\n<li>Saved more than $500,000 annually by decreasing taxpayers share of rising employee health care costs.</li>\r\n<li>Terminated the personal use of city vehicles except for police and fire.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2>Maintained Financial Strength</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Issued no incremental new debt and maintained healthy cash reserves.</li>\r\n<li>Maintained Standard and Poors very strong credit rating of a AA-.\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Fiscal Responsibility', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'fiscal-responsibility', '', '', '2015-01-14 08:45:55', '2015-01-14 08:45:55', '', 10, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/?page_id=178', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(179, 1, '2015-01-06 07:33:41', '2015-01-06 07:33:41', '', 'Fiscal Responsibility', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '178-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-06 07:33:41', '2015-01-06 07:33:41', '', 178, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/178-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(180, 1, '2015-01-06 07:33:52', '2015-01-06 07:33:52', '<div class="main_heading full_width top_margin top_margin">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Met Demand for Expanded Services With No Additional Tax Burden</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<p class="top_margin">Mayor Kristen Brown has met the communitys demand for expanded City services with no increase in taxes and after eliminating the mandatory trash fees.</p>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Services1.png" alt="Services" width="1002" height="382" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-442" /></div>\r\n<ul class="top_padding">\r\n<li>Curbside Recycling - Formed a public-private partnership enabling the City to provide a curbside recycling service for residents for no additional fees and free 96 gallon toters for single-stream collection, no sorting required.</li>\r\n<li>Animal Care Services Achieved a 100-percent adoption rate for healthy dogs for the last three years.  Animal Care Services has for the first time found all dogs loving, permanent homes, eliminating the need for euthanasia due to space constraints at our shelter.  Adoptions of both dogs and cats are at all-time highs. </li>\r\n<li>Transit Service  Will soon add a fifth transit route to include service to and from the west side on SR 46 and expanded week-day hours of all routes to 8 pm.  These changes were the first and second most requested service improvements by transit customers.</li>\r\n<li>School Resource Officers - In partnership with the school system, dedicated two police officers in the schools to improve our kids safety and to encourage children and teens to avoid drugs, bullying and violence.</li>\r\n<li>Began cost-sharing program with homeowners to repair sidewalks and curbs.</li>\r\n<li>Shared Cost Sidewalk and Curb Program  Introduced the Shared Cost Sidewalk and Curb Program, a cost-sharing program for homeowners to address overdue repairs to sidewalks and curbs.  The program offers outstanding value to homeowners and increases the safety and appearances of our neighborhoods. </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Expanded Services', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'expanded-services', '', '', '2015-01-14 08:06:24', '2015-01-14 08:06:24', '', 10, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/?page_id=180', 0, 'page', '', 0),
