(228, 1, '2015-01-06 12:34:46', '2015-01-06 12:34:46', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Restored and Improved Our Parks and Community Facilities</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="blue_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n  <div class="inner_blue_container">\r\n    <p class="btm_padding">We have an outstanding parks system that provides fun-filled, healthy experiences and lifetime memories for our kids and families.</p>\r\n  <p class="btm_padding">Unfortunately, capital maintenance and repairs to our parks and community facilities had been deferred for many years, leading to significant facilities deterioration, and in some cases, non-functional and unsafe conditions. </p>\r\n  <p class="btm_padding">Community treasures, Hamilton and Donner Centers, were particularly dilapidated and one the verge of being safety hazards.  Some neighborhood parks were badly neglected and had become havens for drug users. </p>\r\n      <p class="btm_padding">Mayor Kristen Brown strongly believes that our parks and community facilities are indispensable and cherished community resources that must be safe, inviting and well-maintained outdoor and indoor spaces.  Under her leadership, the City:</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="img_container"><img src="images/parks.png"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Embarked on an aggressive program to invest 5.5 million public and private dollars to preserve and improve our existing parks and community facilities, including Hamilton and Donner Centers.</li>\r\n<li>Reversed years of neglect and deterioration of our communitys most cherished facilities and ensured they are safe and inviting outdoor and indoor spacesenjoyed by todays and future generations.  </li>\r\n\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Parks', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '168-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-06 12:34:46', '2015-01-06 12:34:46', '', 168, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/168-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(230, 1, '2015-01-06 12:35:02', '2015-01-06 12:35:02', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Restored and Improved Our Parks and Community Facilities</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="blue_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n  <div class="inner_blue_container">\r\n    <p class="btm_padding">We have an outstanding parks system that provides fun-filled, healthy experiences and lifetime memories for our kids and families.</p>\r\n  <p class="btm_padding">Unfortunately, capital maintenance and repairs to our parks and community facilities had been deferred for many years, leading to significant facilities deterioration, and in some cases, non-functional and unsafe conditions. </p>\r\n  <p class="btm_padding">Community treasures, Hamilton and Donner Centers, were particularly dilapidated and one the verge of being safety hazards.  Some neighborhood parks were badly neglected and had become havens for drug users. </p>\r\n      <p class="btm_padding">Mayor Kristen Brown strongly believes that our parks and community facilities are indispensable and cherished community resources that must be safe, inviting and well-maintained outdoor and indoor spaces.  Under her leadership, the City:</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="img_container"><a href="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/parks.png"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/parks.png" alt="parks" width="370" height="498" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-229" /></a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Embarked on an aggressive program to invest 5.5 million public and private dollars to preserve and improve our existing parks and community facilities, including Hamilton and Donner Centers.</li>\r\n<li>Reversed years of neglect and deterioration of our communitys most cherished facilities and ensured they are safe and inviting outdoor and indoor s