redevelopment will provide much-needed addition high-quality, affordable housing and an assisted living facility.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Neighborhoods', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '172-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-06 12:39:11', '2015-01-06 12:39:11', '', 172, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/172-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(239, 1, '2015-01-06 12:40:03', '2015-01-06 12:40:03', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Revitalized and Strengthened Our Neighborhoods</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<p class="top_margin">Mayor Kristen Brown has taken a comprehensive approach to revitalization and made tremendous progress making our more challenged neighborhoods safer, prouder and free of blight.  Since assuming office, she and her administration have:</p>\r\n<img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Neighborhoods.png" alt="Neighborhoods" width="988" height="496" class="top_margin full_width" />\r\n<ul class="top_margin">\r\n<li>Substantially improved conditions in our neighborhoods through regular neighborhood meetings, community policing, cleanup projects, and code enforcement.</li>\r\n<li>Turned 9th Street Neighborhood Park into a safe and inviting place for kids to play from what it had become: a magnet for anti-social behavior and criminal activity, particularly drug-related issues.</li>\r\n<li>Ordered the demolishment or repair of twenty-three abandoned, blighted and unsafe homes and commercial buildings.</li>\r\n<li>Begun the Citys first ever Blight Elimination Program with a $760,000 grant to fund the demolishment of approximately three dozen abandoned and blighted houses.</li>\r\n<li>Completed the State Street Revitalization Plan to redevelop State Street and revitalize the surrounding neighborhoods. Mayor Brown voted in favor of funding and implementing the first phase of the State Street Plan this year.</li>\r\n<li>Partnered with two private developers to remediate and redevelop the Golden Castings Foundry site, a decade-long source of blight in the heart of our city.  The redevelopment will provide much-needed addition high-quality, affordable housing and an assisted living facility.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Neighborhoods', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '172-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-06 12:40:03', '2015-01-06 12:40:03', '', 172, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/172-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(240, 1, '2015-01-06 12:40:46', '2015-01-06 12:40:46', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Ushered in New Era of Good Government</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="blue_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n  <div class="inner_blue_container">\r\n    <p>Mayor Kristen Brown believes that how government operates is every bit as important as what it accomplishes.  Her goal is to be the most honest, transparent, inclusive, responsive and accountable municipal government of our size.  And shes delivering.  </p>\r\n    <p class="btm_padding">Mayor Brown and her administration have:</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="img_container"><img src="images/government.png"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Operated transparently, responsively, ethically and with accountability.</li>\r\n<li>Dissolved the Citys private corporation, CDI, and stopped spending taxpayer money behind closed doors.</li>\r\n<li>Began live and on-demand broadcasting of public meetings on the internet.</li>\r\n<li>Passed comprehensive code of ethical conduct.</li>\r\n<li>Attained national accreditation by the Columbus Police Department.</li>\r\n<li>Dramatically improved city governments transparency with live and on-demand broadcasting of public meetings online. This service has attracted thousands of views.</li>\r\n<li>Gained adoption of a comprehensive code of ethical conduct, helping assure you that public officials and employees are operating in your best interest  not in their own personal interests or in favor of special interests.</li>\r\n<li>Attained accreditation for the police department, ensuring our officers maintain the highest professional standards and operate with the utmost integrity, transparency and accountability.  Only three percent of the law enforcement agencies in the nation achieve this status.</li>\r\n<li>Improved service by launching uReport, an online customer service request application that gives you the opportunity to quickly and easily request city services.</li>\r\n<li>Developed a long-term strategic plan for city government with priorities and measurable objectives and published annual reports detailing results.</li>\r\n<li>Achieved a finding-free audit from the Indiana State Board of Accounts in 2013.</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Good Government', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '176-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-06 12:40:46', '2015-01-06 12:40:46', '', 176, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/176-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(241, 1, '2015-01-06 12:41:07', '2015-01-06 12:41:07', '', 'government', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'government', '', '', '2015-01-06 12:41:07', '2015-01-06 12:41:07', '', 176, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/government.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
(242, 1, '2015-01-06 12:41:10', '2015-01-06 12:41:10', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Ushered in New Era of Good Government</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="blue_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n  <div class="inner_blue_container">\r\n    <p>Mayor Kristen Brown believes that how government operates is every bit as important as what it accomplishes.  Her goal is to be the most honest, transparent, inclusive, responsive and accountable municipal government of our size.  And shes delivering.  </p>\r\n    <p class="btm_padding">Mayor Brown and her administration have:</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="img_container"><a href="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/government.png"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/government.png" alt="government" width="482" height="263" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-241" /></a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Operated transparently, responsively, ethically and with accountability.</li>\r\n<li>Dissolved the Citys private corporation, CDI, and stopped spending taxpayer money behind closed doors.</li>\r\n<li>Began live and on-demand broadcasting of public meetings on the internet.</li>\r\n<li>Passed comprehensive code of ethical conduct.</li>\r\n<li>Attained national accreditation by the Columbus Police Department.</li>\r\n<li>Dramatically improved city governments transparency with live and on-demand broadcasting of public meetings online. This service has attracted thousands of views.</li>\r\n<li>Gained adoption of a comprehensive code of ethical conduct, helping assure you that public officials and employees are operating in your best interest  not in their own personal interests or in favor of special interests.</li>\r\n<li>Attained accreditation for the police department, ensuring our officers maintain the highest professional standards and operate with the utmost integrity, transparency and accountability.  Only three percent of the law enforcement agencies in the nation achieve this status.</li>\r\n<li>Improved service by launching uReport, an online customer service request application that gives you the opportunity to quickly and easily request city services.</li>\r\n<li>Developed a long-term strategic plan for city government with priorities and measurable objectives and published annual reports detailing results.</li>\r\n<li>Achieved a finding-free audit from the Indiana State Board of Accounts in 2013.</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Good Government', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '176-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-06 12:41:10', '2015-01-06 12:41:10', '', 176, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/176-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
