(259, 1, '2015-01-07 09:46:35', '2015-01-07 09:46:35', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Mayor Kristen Brown</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2 class="top_margin">A Hometown Girl with a Passion for Columbus</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Mayor Kristen Brown is a native of Columbus with humble beginnings.  She has deep roots in the community: a sixth generation resident of Bartholomew County on her mothers side of the family and a fourth generation resident of Columbus on her fathers side.</li>\r\n<li>Mayor Browns love for Columbus, her passion to serve the people and her capability and courage to make a positive difference led her to run for mayor of her hometown.</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2 >A Champion of the People Elected with Mandate for Change</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Kristen Brown was elected the 36th Mayor of the City of Columbus in a wave of popular support in 2011.  She won the Republican primary in a landslide and by a margin of 3:1 over both of the political establishments picks on the Republican ticket.  She then won the general election by a margin of more than 2 to 1 and after receiving more votes than any mayoral candidate in the citys history.  </li>\r\n<li>Voters placed their confidence in Kristen Brown to make government better and more inclusive and to advance Columbus toward an even brighter future.</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2 >A Public Servant Who Has Kept Her Promises and More</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Since assuming office on January 1, 2012, she has delivered on every one of her campaign promises and more.  </li>\r\n<li>Mayor Brown has lowered taxes, improved services, particularly public safety, provided the environment that ensures our employers prosper and create good jobs, made the tough calls to get our fiscal house in order and made city government accountable and ensured it operates with integrity, transparency a strong citizen voice.</li>\r\n<li>She has also invested in vital public infrastructure, repairing our roads and parks facilities and reversing years of deferred investment and neglect.  Shes strengthened our neighborhoods and eliminated blight.  Shes met the communitys demand for expanded services with no tax increase.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2 >A Leader with Vision and a Plan</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Mayor Brown, in partnership with the community, developed Columbus first community-wide strategic plan and process, Advance Columbus.  Advance Columbus paints a bold vision for Columbus, defines the communitys highest strategic priorities, leaving no one behind, and sets out the solutions and processes for advancing Columbus toward its vision.  Advance Columbus is already achieving tangible results.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2 >A Proven, Qualified Leader</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Prior to serving as Mayor, Mayor Brown came from a successful career in business, holding numerous positions of increasing responsibility in the fields of banking, investment management and the computer software industry.  Brown was a senior executive and Vice President of several leading companies including publicly-traded giants Oracle and Intuit, the developer of Quickbooks, Quicken and TurboTax.</li>\r\n<li>Brown graduated at the top of her class from Columbus North High School in 1982. She graduated from Brown University with a B.A., magna cum laude, in 1986 and from Harvard University with an M.B.A in 1993.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n', 'About''s Kristen', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '14-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-07 09:46:35', '2015-01-07 09:46:35', '', 14, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/14-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(260, 1, '2015-01-07 09:47:02', '2015-01-07 09:47:02', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">You Can Help</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin ">\r\n<p class="btm_padding" >Together, we took back our community in the mayors race in 2011.  In the Republican primary on this May 5th, the choices are clear.  We can go back to politics as usual and taking your tax dollars or we can continue to positively change our governments course, protect your tax dollars and advance Columbus toward our vision.  </p>\r\n<p  class="btm_padding" >But we need you again to make it happen and we hope youll join our team.  \r\n  </p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2>I WOULD LIKE TO HELP KRISTEN BY:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>PLACING A YARD SIGN IN MY YARD</li>\r\n<li>GOING DOOR TO DOOR</li>\r\n<li>MAKING PHONE CALLS </li>\r\n<li>OTHER ACTIVITIES IF AVAILABLE</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div class="form_part full_width top_margin">\r\n<div class="form_left">\r\n<div class="full_width form_left_container">\r\n<div class="form_text"><p>First Name<span>*</span></p></div>\r\n<div class="form_input_box"><input type="text"></div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="full_width form_left_container">\r\n<div class="form_text"><p> Street Address<span>*</span></p></div>\r\n<div class="form_input_box"><textarea type="text"></textarea></div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="full_width form_left_container">\r\n<div class="form_text"><p>Email<span>*</span></p></div>\r\n<div class="form_input_box"><input type="text"></div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class="form_right">\r\n<div class="full_width form_left_container">\r\n<div class="form_text"><p>Last Name<span>*</span></p></div>\r\n<div class="form_input_box"><input type="text"></div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="full_width form_left_container">\r\n<div class="form_text"><p>Zip Code<span>*</span></p></div>\r\n<div class="form_input_box"><input type="text"></div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="full_width form_left_container top_padding">\r\n<div class="form_text"><p>Phone<span>*</span></p></div>\r\n<div class="form_input_box"><input type="text"></div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="full_width form_botton1">\r\n<input type="submit" value="Submit">\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<p class="top_margin text_align" >Thank you for your interest in advancing Columbus! The campaign team will be in touch with you soon</p>\r\n\r\n</div>', 'You Can Help', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '16-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-07 09:47:02', '2015-01-07 09:47:02', '', 16, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/16-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(261, 1, '2015-01-07 09:49:48', '2015-01-07 09:49:48', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Encouraged Job Growth</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<p class="top_margin">\r\n Under Mayor Kristen Browns leadership, Columbus has set records for the number of jobs and employment.  The </p>\r\n <div class="blue_text_container full_width ">\r\n  <div class="inner_blue_container">\r\n    <p>Columbus metropolitan area is at all-time record highs for \r\nboth the number of jobs in our community  more than \r\n51,000 - and the number of residents who are employed \r\n more than 41,000.   Our unemployment rate is currently \r\nonly 4% - the second lowest in the state.During Mayor \r\n Browns first term:</p>\r\n <ul>\r\n<li>Set all-time records for jobs and employment, second lowest \r\nunemployment rate in the state.</li>\r\n<li>Reaffirmed Cummins commitment to Columbus with \r\nannouncement of 500 new jobs.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="img_container"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/jobs.png" alt="jobs" width="486" height="322" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-224" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n <div class="full_width">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Encouraged the creation of more than another 500 new industrial jobs and investments of nearly $250 million.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2>And the City of Columbus:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Provided tax incentives, encouraging the creation of more than another 500 new jobs and investments of nearly $250 million.</li>\r\n<li>Developed a preliminary plan to redevelop the nearly 600 acres of the former Walesboro Airport into an industrial park to provide shovel-ready industrial sites for continued job-creating growth.ts.</li>\r\n<li>Developed the citys first Strategic Growth Plan to readily and efficiently accommodate the citys growth outside todays city limits.</li>\r\n<li>Formed a public-private partnership to develop a 114-bed, $5 million student housing complex at the airport.  This is the game-changer for our four colleges recruitment efforts and our ability to produce a steady pipeline of skilled and educated workers that our employers need to prosper.</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Jobs', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '174-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-07 09:49:48', '2015-01-07 09:49:48', '', 174, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/174-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
