(307, 1, '2015-01-07 12:37:30', '2015-01-07 12:37:30', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n        <h1 class="red_color ">Advance Quality Infrastructure</h1>\r\n        <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n      </div>\r\n     <div class="plan_inner_part full_width top_margin">\r\n          <h2 class="red_color btm_padding1">Investing in Vital Public Infrastructure</h2>\r\n     <p class="btm_padding">Mayor Kristen Brown is committed to the continuation of significant investments in roads, our most critical public infrastructure, without raising taxes.   Mayor Browns plan includes:</p>\r\n     <img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Infrastructure.png" alt="Infrastructure" width="1001" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-288" />\r\n     </div>\r\n     <div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n<h2>Repaired and Rebuilt Our Roads</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Invest another $10+ million to repair our existing roads.</li>\r\n<li>Partner with Indiana Department of Transportation (INDOT) and Louisville & Indiana Railroad to construct an overpass over the railroad tracks at the intersection of state roads 46 and 11 to alleviate severe traffic backups caused by increasing train traffic.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Construct an extension of Maple Street from Tipton Lane to U.S. 31 to give pedestrians, bicyclists and motorists significantly safer routes through the four-school campus area.</li>\r\n<li>Reconstruct the section of Rocky Ford between Taylor Road and Tally Road to widen lanes and add a two-way left turn lane, bicycle lanes, storm sewer system, sidewalks and pedestrian crossings at key locations.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Advance Columbus', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '292-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-07 12:37:30', '2015-01-07 12:37:30', '', 292, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/292-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(309, 1, '2015-01-12 08:19:18', '2015-01-12 08:19:18', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\n        <h1 class="red_color ">A Plan for the Future:  Advance Columbus</h1>\n        <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\n      </div>\n     <div class="plan_text_container full_width top_margin">\n     <div class="inner_blue_container"><p class="btm_padding">Our community is a special and remarkable combination of people and place.  World-renown architecture is woven into the fabric of our daily lives. We benefit from exciting cultural and recreational amenities, a diverse population, a strong sense of community and teamwork and a commitment to excellence. </p>\n     <p>Our local economy is a powerhouse relative to the rest of the state and nation.  The number of jobs in our community is at an all-time high.  The number of residents employed is also at an all-time high.</p></div>\n     <div class="plan_rightPart"></div>\n     </div>\n     <div class="plan_inner_part full_width">\n     <p class="btm_padding">By every major measure, our quality of life in Columbus, Indiana is far better than the state and even the nation as a whole.\nBut we are Columbus.  We aim even higher and we have an unshakable confidence in our ability to create an even more remarkable future.</p>\n     <h2 class="red_color btm_padding1">OUR VISION</h2>\n     <p class="btm_padding">Our vision is <strong>to be the very best community of its size in the country. </strong> It is a bold and ambitious vision.</p>\n     <h2 class="blue_color btm_padding1 ">ONE CITY. ONE PLAN. ADVANCE COLUMBUS.</h2>\n      <p class="btm_padding1">In order to advance Columbus toward this future, Mayor Kristen Brown partnered with the leaders of several other public and private organizations dedicated to serving our community. Together with much public engagement, they created Advance Columbus, a roadmap to solve our toughest challenges, leverage our greatest strengths and capitalize on our many opportunities to advance our quality of life for today and for future generations. </p>\n      <p class="btm_padding1">Mayor Kristen Brown rolled out Advance Columbus at her State of the City address in 2013. </p>\n            <p class="btm_padding1">She also made it the City of Columbus mission to do its part in advancing Columbus toward the future we envision.  Last year, Mayor Brown and department heads developed the City governments first strategic plan, aligning the city governments priorities with the communitys highest priorities as defined by Advance Columbus.  </p>\n            <p class="btm_padding1 blue_color_normal">The plans priorities are to: </p>\n<p class="btm_padding1">1.   Advance Quality Infrastructure<br>\n2.   Advance Economic Prosperity and Well-Paying Jobs<br>\n3.   Advance the Safety and Health of Our Community</p>\n            <p class="btm_padding1">Recognizing that how we get there is every bit as important as getting there, Mayor Browns plan importantly includes advancing Columbus in a way that is consistent with the <a href="">values of good government.</a> </p>\n\n     </div>', 'Advance Columbus', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '292-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-01-12 08:19:18', '2015-01-12 08:19:18', '', 292, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/292-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(310, 1, '2015-01-07 12:44:33', '2015-01-07 12:44:33', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n        <h1 class="red_color ">Advance Quality Infrastructure</h1>\r\n        <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n      </div>\r\n     <div class="plan_inner_part full_width top_margin">\r\n          <h2 class="red_color btm_padding1">Investing in Vital Public Infrastructure</h2>\r\n     <p class="btm_padding">Mayor Kristen Brown is committed to the continuation of significant investments in roads, our most critical public infrastructure, without raising taxes.   Mayor Browns plan includes:</p>\r\n     <img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Infrastructure.png" alt="Infrastructure" width="1001" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-308" />\r\n     </div>\r\n     <div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n<h2>Repaired and Rebuilt Our Roads</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Invest another $10+ million to repair our existing roads.</li>\r\n<li>Partner with Indiana Department of Transportation (INDOT) and Louisville & Indiana Railroad to construct an overpass over the railroad tracks at the intersection of state roads 46 and 11 to alleviate severe traffic backups caused by increasing train traffic.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Construct an extension of Maple Street from Tipton Lane to U.S. 31 to give pedestrians, bicyclists and motorists significantly safer routes through the four-school campus area.</li>\r\n<li>Reconstruct the section of Rocky Ford between Taylor Road and Tally Road to widen lanes and add a two-way left turn lane, bicycle lanes, storm sewer system, sidewalks and pedestrian crossings at key locations.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Advance Columbus', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '292-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-07 12:44:33', '2015-01-07 12:44:33', '', 292, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/292-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
