(342, 1, '2015-01-07 13:58:03', '2015-01-07 13:58:03', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n        <h1 class="red_color ">Advance Opportunities for All</h1>\r\n        <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n      </div>\r\n     <div class="plan_inner_part full_width top_margin">\r\n          <h2 class="red_color btm_padding1">Quality Neighborhoods and Housing for All</h2>\r\n     <p class="btm_padding">Goal:   Ensure safe and proud neighborhoods and quality affordable housing for all.\r\nMayor Kristen Browns plan revitalizes and strengthens our neighborhoods and business corridors by the elimination of blight and through rehabilitation and redevelopment, including the development of quality affordable housing.</p>\r\n<img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/party-safe-teen-project-2.jpg" alt="party-safe-teen-project-2" width="1001" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-308" />\r\n     </div>\r\n     <div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Revitalize and Redevelop State Street Corridor according to our plan.</li>\r\n<li>Revitalize our neighborhoods through infrastructure improvements, stronger property maintenance codes, code enforcement, blight elimination programs, neighborhood cleanups and incentives for private investment in targeted revitalization areas.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Increase the number of affordable housing units in our community through public-private partnerships.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Advance Opportunities for All', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '270-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-07 13:58:03', '2015-01-07 13:58:03', '', 270, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/270-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(343, 1, '2015-01-07 14:00:00', '2015-01-07 14:00:00', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n        <h1 class="red_color ">A Plan for the Future:  Advance Columbus</h1>\r\n        <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n      </div>\r\n     <div class="plan_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n     <div class="plan_leftPart"><p class="btm_padding">Our community is a special and remarkable combination of people and place.  World-renown architecture is woven into the fabric of our daily lives. We benefit from exciting cultural and recreational amenities, a diverse population, a strong sense of community and teamwork and a commitment to excellence. </p>\r\n     <p>Our local economy is a powerhouse relative to the rest of the state and nation.  The number of jobs in our community is at an all-time high.  The number of residents employed is also at an all-time high.</p></div>\r\n     <div class="plan_rightPart"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/plan.png" alt="plan" width="438" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-266" /></div>\r\n     </div>\r\n     <div class="plan_inner_part full_width">\r\n     <p class="btm_padding">By every major measure, our quality of life in Columbus, Indiana is far better than the state and even the nation as a whole.\r\nBut we are Columbus.  We aim even higher and we have an unshakable confidence in our ability to create an even more remarkable future.</p>\r\n     <h2 class="red_color btm_padding1">OUR VISION</h2>\r\n     <p class="btm_padding">Our vision is <strong>to be the very best community of its size in the country. </strong> It is a bold and ambitious vision.</p>\r\n     <h2 class="blue_color btm_padding1 ">ONE CITY. ONE PLAN. ADVANCE COLUMBUS.</h2>\r\n      <p class="btm_padding1">In order to advance Columbus toward this future, Mayor Kristen Brown partnered with the leaders of several other public and private organizations dedicated to serving our community. Together with much public engagement, they created Advance Columbus, a roadmap to solve our toughest challenges, leverage our greatest strengths and capitalize on our many opportunities to advance our quality of life for today and for future generations. </p>\r\n      <p class="btm_padding1">Mayor Kristen Brown rolled out Advance Columbus at her State of the City address in 2013. </p>\r\n            <p class="btm_padding1">She also made it the City of Columbus mission to do its part in advancing Columbus toward the future we envision.  Last year, Mayor Brown and department heads developed the City governments first strategic plan, aligning the city governments priorities with the communitys highest priorities as defined by Advance Columbus.  </p>\r\n            <p class="btm_padding1 blue_color_normal">The plans priorities are to: </p>\r\n<p class="btm_padding1">1.   Advance Quality Infrastructure<br>\r\n2.   Advance Economic Prosperity and Well-Paying Jobs<br>\r\n3.   Advance the Safety and Health of Our Community</p>\r\n            <p class="btm_padding1">Recognizing that how we get there is every bit as important as getting there, Mayor Browns plan importantly includes advancing Columbus in a way that is consistent with the <a href="">values of good government.</a> </p>\r\n\r\n     </div>', 'Advance Columbus', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '292-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-07 14:00:00', '2015-01-07 14:00:00', '', 292, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/292-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(344, 1, '2015-01-07 14:01:49', '2015-01-07 14:01:49', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n        <h1 class="red_color ">Advance the Safety and Health of Our Community</h1>\r\n        <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n      </div>\r\n     <div class="plan_inner_part full_width top_margin">\r\n          <h2 class="red_color btm_padding1">Investing in Vital Public Infrastructure</h2>\r\n     <p class="btm_padding">Mayor Kristen Brown is committed to the continuation of significant investments in roads, our most critical public infrastructure, without raising taxes.   Mayor Browns plan includes:</p>\r\n     <img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Infrastructure.png" alt="Infrastructure" width="1001" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-308" />\r\n     </div>\r\n     <div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n<h2>Repaired and Rebuilt Our Roads</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Invest another $10+ million to repair our existing roads.</li>\r\n<li>Partner with Indiana Department of Transportation (INDOT) and Louisville & Indiana Railroad to construct an overpass over the railroad tracks at the intersection of state roads 46 and 11 to alleviate severe traffic backups caused by increasing train traffic.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Construct an extension of Maple Street from Tipton Lane to U.S. 31 to give pedestrians, bicyclists and motorists significantly safer routes through the four-school campus area.</li>\r\n<li>Reconstruct the section of Rocky Ford between Taylor Road and Tally Road to widen lanes and add a two-way left turn lane, bicycle lanes, storm sewer system, sidewalks and pedestrian crossings at key locations.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Advance the Safety and Health of Our Community', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '297-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-07 14:01:49', '2015-01-07 14:01:49', '', 297, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/297-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(345, 1, '2015-01-07 14:04:04', '2015-01-07 14:04:04', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1>Made Columbus Safer, Protected You and Your Family</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="safety_part full_width">\r\n<div class="blue_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n  <div class="inner_blue_container">\r\n    <p class="btm_padding">Along with maintaining and improving our public infrastructure, public safety is job number one for Mayor Kristen Brown.<br><span class="red_color">Accelerated Law Enforcement Efforts</span> Under Mayor Browns leadership, we have more police officers on our streets than at any time in our citys history and never before have they been more productive. She and her administration have:</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n ', 'Public Safety', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '170-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-07 14:04:04', '2015-01-07 14:04:04', '', 170, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/170-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(346, 1, '2015-01-07 14:05:07', '2015-01-07 14:05:07', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1>Made Columbus Safer, Protected You and Your Family</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="safety_part full_width">\r\n<div class="blue_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n  <div class="inner_blue_container">\r\n    <p class="btm_padding">Along with maintaining and improving our public infrastructure, public safety is job number one for Mayor Kristen Brown.<br><span class="red_color">Accelerated Law Enforcement Efforts</span> Under Mayor Browns leadership, we have more police officers on our streets than at any time in our citys history and never before have they been more productive. She and her administration have:</p>\r\n    \r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="img_container"><a href="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/safety.png"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/safety.png" alt="safety" width="609" height="307" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-232" /></a></div>\r\n</div></div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Choked the flow of dangerous drugs into our community, increasing drug-related arrests by 37% last year.</li>\r\n<li>Dramatically increased proactive community policing by all patrol officers and a new dedicated community policing unit, resulting a \r\n45% increase in community policing patrols.</li>\r\n<li>Significantly reduced property crime and restoring stability to our hardest-hit neighborhoods.</li>\r\n<li>Reduced the number of traffic accidents through an acceleration of traffic enforcement efforts.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2>Improved Emergency Medical Services and Saved Tax Dollars</h2>\r\n<p>Mayor Kristen Brown and her team have significantly advanced emergency medical services, ensuring residents have the best chance for surviving a life-threatening event.  The City has:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Awarded a new ambulance contract to Columbus Regional Hospital after conducting a fair, transparent and competitive bidding processresulting in significantly improved service and reduced costs to taxpayers from nearly $1 million every year to $0 a year.</li>\r\n<li>ncreased the number of paramedic firefighterscertified in advanced life-support techniques tostaff one on all six engines at every fire station every day.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2>ImprovedRescue, Disaster and Extreme Weather Response</h2>\r\n<p>Mayor Kristen Brown has ensured that we are well prepared for the myriad of threats our community faces.  Mayor Brown and her team:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Sold the mayors city-owned vehicle to fund ice water rescue equipment for City firefighters to ensure optimal victim survivability around the citys 161 ponds and lakes.</li>\r\n<li>Unveiled the first-ever Flood Risk Warning and Management Plan on the fifth tanniversary of the 2008 flood. Never again will we be unprepared.</li>\r\n<li>Deployed an emergency notification system that sends alerts to citizens by voicemail, text messages and emails during emergencies.</li>\r\n<li>Ensured that our roads were cleared of snow and ice and potholes were patched in a timely manner during extreme winter weather the last two years.</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Public Safety', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '170-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-07 14:05:07', '2015-01-07 14:05:07', '', 170, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/170-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(347, 1, '2015-01-15 01:37:31', '2015-01-15 01:37:31', '<div class="main_heading full_width top_margin">\n<h1>Made Columbus Safer, Protected You and Your Family</h1>\n<div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin">\n<p class="btm_padding">Along with maintaining and improving our public infrastructure, public safety is job number one for Mayor Kristen Brown.</p>\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-613" src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/safety2.png" alt="safety" />\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2>Accelerated Law Enforcement Efforts</h2>\nUnder Mayor Browns leadership, we have more police officers on our streets than at any time in our citys history and never before have they been more productive.\n<ul>\n	<li>Choked the flow of dangerous drugs into our community by cracking down on a threefold increase in the number of dealers of methamphetamine and heroin.</li>\n	<li>Restored stability to our hardest-hit neighborhoods with a 45% increase in community policing patrols and a new dedicated community policing unit.</li>\n	<li>Cut violent crime nearly in half and cut property crime by 23%. Reduced the number of traffic accidents through an acceleration of traffic enforcement efforts.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\n<h2>Improved Emergency Medical Services and Saved Tax Dollars</h2>\nMayor Kristen Brown and her team have significantly advanced emergency medical services, ensuring residents have the best chance for surviving a life-threatening event.\n<ul>\n	<li>Awarded a new ambulance contract to Columbus Regional Hospital after conducting a fair, transparent and competitive bidding process resulting in significantly improved service and reduced costs to taxpayers from nearly $1 million every year to $0 a year.</li>\n	<li>Increased the number of paramedic firefighters certified in advanced life-support techniques to staff one on all six engines at every fire station every day.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\n<h2>Improved Rescue, Disaster and Extreme Weather Response</h2>\nMayor Kristen Brown and her team have ensured that we are well prepared for the myriad of threats our community faces.\n<ul>\n	<li>Sold the mayors city-owned vehicle to fund ice water rescue equipment for City firefighters to ensure optimal victim survivability around the citys 161 ponds and lakes.</li>\n	<li>Unveiled the first-ever Flood Risk Warning and Management Plan on the fifth anniversary of the 2008 flood. Never again will we be unprepared.</li>\n	<li>Deployed an emergency notification system that sends alerts to citizens by voicemail, text messages and emails during emergencies.</li>\n	<li>Ensured that our roads were cleared of snow and ice and potholes were patched in a timely manner during extreme winter weather the last two years.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>', 'Public Safety', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '170-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-01-15 01:37:31', '2015-01-15 01:37:31', '', 170, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/170-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
