(366, 1, '2015-01-07 14:26:50', '2015-01-07 14:26:50', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n        <h1 class="red_color ">Advance the Safety and Health of Our Community</h1>\r\n        <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n      </div>\r\n     <div class="plan_inner_part full_width top_margin">\r\n      \r\n     <p class="btm_padding">We are one of the safest communities in the country. However, when it comes to our personal safety and the protection of our property, there will always be room for improvement. A healthy community includes living healthy lifestyles and living in an environmentally safe community.</p>\r\n     </div>\r\n<div class="safety_part full_width">\r\n<div class="blue_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n  <div class="inner_blue_container">\r\n    <p class="btm_padding">Mayor Kristen Browns goals for a safe and healthy community include:<br><span class="red_color">Safest Community</span>\r\nGoal:  Be the safest city of our size in the country.\r\nMayor Kristen Browns plan calls for sustaining and advancing your and your familys safety as her highest priority.\r\nThankfully, our violent crime is in the lowest ten percent of the nation.  However, dangerous drugs are prevalent in our community.  Not only does drug abuse destroy the lives of users and families, it is fueling a property crime rate that is unacceptably high.  Mayor Browns priority is to:</p>\r\n    \r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="img_container"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Mayors-Motocycle-Ride-1.jpg" alt="Mayors-Motocycle-Ride-1" width="609" height="447" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-362" /></div>\r\n</div></div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Stem the tide of dangerous drugs into our community and cut our property crime rate by continuing to accelerate our narcotics investigations and community policing efforts and by leveraging technology as a force multiplier.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2>Healthy Community</h2>\r\n<p>Goal:  Radically improve the health and wellness of our residents through healthy behaviors, healthy lifestyles and access to healthcare.\r\nObesity, substance abuse and mental illness remain the most vexing health problems facing us today.  Were making great progress on these fronts but we have much more work to do.\r\nMayor Kristen Browns plan ensures that the community collectively supports both mental and physical wellness.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Cut the demand for drugs in our community through significantly greater leadership and resources directed toward prevention and treatment of substance abuse and mental health disorders.  Cutting the supply of drugs will remain a tremendous challenge until we seriously address the demand for drugs in our community.</li>\r\n<li>Build People Bridges, dedicated bike and pedestrian bridges, to make important and safe People Trail connections over our rivers, busy streets and railroad tracks, including the riverfront of the Pump House property, over Lindsey into downtown at the 3rd Street Bridge and over Haw Creek and Central near 3rd Street.</li>\r\n<li>Form a public-private partnership to develop an indoor athletic training facility on the airports property for use by our local sports teams, including soccer, football and other field sports teams.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n', 'Advance the Safety and Health of Our Community', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '297-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-07 14:26:50', '2015-01-07 14:26:50', '', 297, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/297-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
