ity. Together with much public engagement, they created Advance Columbus, a roadmap to solve our toughest challenges, leverage our greatest strengths and capitalize on our many opportunities to advance our quality of life for today and for future generations. </p>\r\n      <p class="btm_padding1">Mayor Kristen Brown rolled out Advance Columbus at her State of the City address in 2013. </p>\r\n            <p class="btm_padding1">She also made it the City of Columbus mission to do its part in advancing Columbus toward the future we envision.  Last year, Mayor Brown and department heads developed the City governments first strategic plan, aligning the city governments priorities with the communitys highest priorities as defined by Advance Columbus.  </p>\r\n            <p class="btm_padding1 blue_color_normal">The plans priorities are to: </p>\r\n<p class="btm_padding1">1.   Advance Quality Infrastructure<br>\r\n2.   Advance Economic Prosperity and Well-Paying Jobs<br>\r\n3.   Advance the Safety and Health of Our Community</p>\r\n            <p class="btm_padding1">Recognizing that how we get there is every bit as important as getting there, Mayor Browns plan importantly includes advancing Columbus in a way that is consistent with the <a href="">values of good government.</a> </p>\r\n\r\n     </div>', 'Advance Columbus', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '292-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-12 08:23:54', '2015-01-12 08:23:54', '', 292, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/292-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(514, 1, '2015-01-12 08:27:32', '2015-01-12 08:27:32', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n<h1 class="red_color ">Advance the Safety and Health of Our Community</h1>\r\n<div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>     \r\n <div class="plan_inner_part full_width top_margin">\r\n        <p class="blue_color_normal">We are one of the safest communities in the country. However, when it comes to our personal safety and the protection of our property, there will always be room for improvement. A healthy community includes living healthy lifestyles and living in an </p>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div class="community_part full_width ">\r\n        <div class="inner_blue_container">\r\n          <p class="blue_color_normal">environmentally safe community.</p>\r\n          <h2 class="red_color btm_padding1">Safest Community</h2>\r\n          <p class=" btm_padding1">Goal:  Be the safest city of our size in the country.</p>\r\n          <p class=" btm_padding1">Mayor Kristen Browns plan calls for sustaining and advancing your and your familys safety as her highest priority.</p>\r\n          <p >Thankfully, our violent crime is in the lowest ten percent of the nation.  However, dangerous drugs are prevalent in our community.  Not only does drug abuse destroy the lives of users and families, it is fueling a property crime rate that is unacceptably high.  Mayor Browns priority is to:</p>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div class="img_container top_margin"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/health1.png" alt="health" width="441" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-410" /></div>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin ">\r\n        <ul>\r\n          <li>Stem the tide of dangerous drugs into our community and cut our property crime rate by continuing to accelerate our narcotics investigations and community policing efforts and by leveraging technology as a force multiplier.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div class="community_btmPart full_width ">\r\n        <div class="inner_text_container full_width ">\r\n          <h2>Healthy Community</h2>\r\n          <p class="top_padding" >Goal:  Radically improve the health and wellness of our residents through healthy behaviors, healthy lifestyles and access to healthcare.</p>\r\n          <p class="top_padding" >Obesity, substance abuse and mental illness remain the most vexing health problems facing us today.  Were making great progress on these fronts but we have much more work to do.</p>\r\n          <p class="top_padding btm_padding1" >Mayor Kristen Browns plan ensures that the community collectively supports both mental and physical wellness. </p>\r\n          <ul>\r\n            <li>Cut the demand for drugs in our community through significantly greater leadership and resources directed toward prevention and treatment of substance abuse and mental health disorders.  Cutting the supply of drugs will remain a tremendous challenge until we seriously address the demand for drugs in our community.</li>\r\n            <li>Build People Bridges, dedicated bike and pedestrian bridges, to make important and safe People Trail connections over our rivers, busy streets and railroad tracks, including the riverfront of the Pump House property, over Lindsey into downtown at the 3rd Street Bridge and over Haw Creek and Central near 3rd Street. </li>\r\n            <li>Form a public-private partnership to develop an indoor athletic training facility on the airports property for use by our local sports teams, including soccer, football and other field sports teams.</li>            \r\n          </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>', 'Advance the Safety and Health of Our Community', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '297-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-12 08:27:32', '2015-01-12 08:27:32', '', 297, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/297-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
