span class="bold_color1">Goal:</span>  Radically improve the health and wellness of our residents through healthy behaviors, healthy lifestyles and access to healthcare.</p>\r\n          <p class="top_padding" >Obesity, substance abuse and mental illness remain the most vexing health problems facing us today.  Were making great progress on these fronts but we have much more work to do.</p>\r\n          <p class="top_padding btm_padding1" >Mayor Kristen Browns plan ensures that the community collectively supports both mental and physical wellness. </p>\r\n          <ul>\r\n            <li>Cut the demand for drugs in our community through significantly greater leadership and resources directed toward prevention and treatment of substance abuse and mental health disorders.  Cutting the supply of drugs will remain a tremendous challenge until we seriously address the demand for drugs in our community.</li>\r\n            <li>Build People Bridges, dedicated bike and pedestrian bridges, to make important and safe People Trail connections over our rivers, busy streets and railroad tracks, including the riverfront of the Pump House property, over Lindsey into downtown at the 3rd Street Bridge and over Haw Creek and Central near 3rd Street. </li>\r\n            <li>Form a public-private partnership to develop an indoor athletic training facility on the airports property for use by our local sports teams, including soccer, football and other field sports teams.</li>            \r\n          </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>', 'Advance the Safety and Health of Our Community', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '297-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-13 04:56:31', '2015-01-13 04:56:31', '', 297, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/297-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
