(556, 1, '2015-01-14 05:25:47', '2015-01-14 05:25:47', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Repaired and Rebuilt Our Roads</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n    <p class="btm_padding1">For years, Columbus underinvested in maintaining its roads.  When Mayor Kristen Brown assumed office, we were far behind schedule and many of our streets were in total disrepair, creating difficult and unsafe driving conditions and wear and tear on our vehicles . Mayor Brown made our most critical infrastructure  a top priority full stop/period  </p>    \r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="inner_text_container full_width"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/roads2.png" alt="roads" width="1001" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-544" /></div>\r\n\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Completed the largest road repair project in the citys history by investing an unprecedented $10 million to reconstruct and resurface 40 miles of crumbling streets.</li>\r\n<li>Completed or began six major road improvement projects for a combined investment of $20 million.</li>\r\n<li>Completed the largest road repair project in the citys history, investing an unprecedented $10 million in three years to reconstruct and resurface approximately 40 miles of crumbling streets.  By comparison the City was spending less than $400,000 repaving only about 4 miles of roads a year prior to her assuming the job of mayor in 2012.</li>\r\n<li>Completed construction or begun the design of six major road improvement projects for a combined investment of more than $20 million funded primarily by federal transportation dollars.</li>\r\n<li>Fourth Street  this $2.2 million in 2012 project transformed 4th Street from Jackson to Lafayette.  Its now pedestrian friendly, accommodates expanded outdoor seating and is readily closed to traffic for community events and celebrations.</li>\r\n<li>200S  this $3 million project in 2013 alleviated traffic congestion and made this old country road, now a suburban collector, significantly safer for motorists, school buses and pedestrians by widening the lanes, adding a left-turn lane, a storm sewer system, a sidewalk and railroad crossing improvements.</li>\r\n<li>Carr Hill Road  this $2.2 million in 2014 project transformed this formercountry road into a suburban collector to better serve the growing residential area on the west side of Columbus. The improved street provide wider traffic lanes, curbs, gutters, storm sewers, bicycle lanes and sidewalks on both sides of the street.</li>\r\n<li>Indiana Avenue  this $7 million project in 2015 will improve this suburban collector serving Columbus East High School and connecting two arterials, Marr Road and State Street, on Columbus east side.  Lanes will be widened and a storm sewer system, bicycle lanes and sidewalks will be added.  Currently the utility relocation is complete and construction will be \r\ncompleted this year.</li>\r\n<li>Rocky Ford Taylor to Talley  this $7 million project in 2016 will transform this old country road into a suburban collector.  It includes widened lanes in each direction, a two-way left turn lane, bicycle lanes, a storm sewer system and sidewalks on both sides of the street. The City is currently acquiring right-of-way for this project and construction is planned in 2016.</li>\r\n<li>Maple Street  this $1 million project will extend Maple Street from Tipton Lane to U.S. 31, giving pedestrians, bicyclists and motorists significantly safer routes and alleviating traffic congestion to and from school in the four-school campus area that includes Columbus North High School, Northside Middle School, Schmitt Elementary School and St. Bartholomew Catholic \r\nSchool. The City is currently in the design engineering phase of this project and construction is planned in 2016.</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Roads', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '166-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-14 05:25:47', '2015-01-14 05:25:47', '', 166, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/166-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(557, 1, '2015-01-14 05:28:14', '2015-01-14 05:28:14', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Restored and Improved Our Parks and Community Facilities</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="blue_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n  <div class="inner_blue_container">\r\n    <p class="btm_padding1">We have an outstanding parks system that provides fun-filled, healthy experiences and lifetime memories for our kids and families.</p>\r\n  <p class="btm_padding1">Unfortunately, capital maintenance and repairs to our parks and community facilities had been deferred for many years, leading to significant facilities deterioration, and in some cases, non-functional and unsafe conditions. </p>\r\n  <p class="btm_padding1">Community treasures, Hamilton and Donner Centers, were particularly dilapidated and one the verge of being safety hazards.  Some neighborhood parks were badly neglected and had become havens for drug users. </p>\r\n      <p class="btm_padding1">Mayor Kristen Brown strongly believes that our parks and community facilities are indispensable and cherished community resources that must be safe, inviting and well-maintained outdoor and indoor spaces.  Under her leadership, the City:</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="img_container"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/parks1.png" alt="parks" width="370" height="498" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-440" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Embarked on an aggressive program to invest 5.5 million public and private dollars to preserve and improve our existing parks and community facilities, including Hamilton and Donner Centers.</li>\r\n<li>Reversed years of neglect and deterioration of our communitys most cherished facilities and ensured they are safe and inviting outdoor and indoor spacesenjoyed by todays and future generations.  </li>\r\n\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Parks', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '168-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-14 05:28:14', '2015-01-14 05:28:14', '', 168, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/168-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(558, 1, '2015-01-14 05:33:23', '2015-01-14 05:33:23', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Advance the Safety and Health of Our Community</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="plan_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n        <p class="blue_color_normal btm_padding1" >We are one of the safest communities in the country. However, when it comes to our personal safety and the protection of our property, there will always be room for improvement. A healthy community includes living healthy lifestyles and living in an environmentally safe community.</p>          \r\n          <h2 class="red_color btm_padding1" >Safest Community</h2>\r\n          <p class=" btm_padding1 blue_color_normal"><span class="blue_color1">Goal:</span> Be the safest city of our size in the country.</p>\r\n          <p class=" btm_padding1 blue_color_normal">Mayor Kristen Browns plan calls for sustaining and advancing your and your familys safety as her highest priority.</p>\r\n          <p class=" blue_color_normal">Thankfully, our violent crime is in the lowest ten percent of the nation.  However, dangerous drugs are prevalent in our community.  Not only does drug abuse destroy the lives of users and families, it is fueling a property crime rate that is unacceptably high.  Mayor Browns priority is to:</p>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div class="nner_text_container full_width top_margin"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/health.png" alt="health" width="1001" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-539" /></div>     \r\n      <div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin ">\r\n        <ul>\r\n          <li>Stem the tide of dangerous drugs into our community and cut our property crime rate by continuing to accelerate our narcotics investigations and community policing efforts and by leveraging technology as a force multiplier.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div class="community_btmPart full_width ">\r\n        <div class="inner_text_container full_width ">\r\n          <h2>Healthy Community</h2>\r\n          <p class="top_padding" ><span class="bold_color1">Goal:</span>  Radically improve the health and wellness of our residents through healthy behaviors, healthy lifestyles and access to healthcare.</p>\r\n          <p class="top_padding" >Obesity, substance abuse and mental illness remain the most vexing health problems facing us today.  Were making great progress on these fronts but we have much more work to do.</p>\r\n          <p class="top_padding btm_padding1" >Mayor Kristen Browns plan ensures that the community collectively supports both mental and physical wellness. </p>\r\n          <ul>\r\n            <li>Cut the demand for drugs in our community through significantly greater leadership and resources directed toward prevention and treatment of substance abuse and mental health disorders.  Cutting the supply of drugs will remain a tremendous challenge until we seriously address the demand for drugs in our community.</li>\r\n            <li>Build People Bridges, dedicated bike and pedestrian bridges, to make important and safe People Trail connections over our rivers, busy streets and railroad tracks, including the riverfront of the Pump House property, over Lindsey into downtown at the 3rd Street Bridge and over Haw Creek and Central near 3rd Street. </li>\r\n            <li>Form a public-private partnership to develop an indoor athletic training facility on the airports property for use by our local sports teams, including soccer, football and other field sports teams.</li>            \r\n          </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>', 'Advance the Safety and Health of Our Community', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '297-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-14 05:33:23', '2015-01-14 05:33:23', '', 297, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/297-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(559, 1, '2015-01-14 05:34:28', '2015-01-14 05:34:28', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Advance the Safety and Health of Our Community</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="plan_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n        <p class="blue_color_normal btm_padding1" >We are one of the safest communities in the country. However, when it comes to our personal safety and the protection of our property, there will always be room for improvement. A healthy community includes living healthy lifestyles and living in an environmentally safe community.</p>          \r\n          <h2 class="red_color btm_padding1" >Safest Community</h2>\r\n          <p class=" btm_padding1 blue_color_normal"><span class="blue_color1">Goal:</span> Be the safest city of our size in the country.</p>\r\n          <p class=" btm_padding1 blue_color_normal">Mayor Kristen Browns plan calls for sustaining and advancing your and your familys safety as her highest priority.</p>\r\n          <p class=" blue_color_normal">Thankfully, our violent crime is in the lowest ten percent of the nation.  However, dangerous drugs are prevalent in our community.  Not only does drug abuse destroy the lives of users and families, it is fueling a property crime rate that is unacceptably high.  Mayor Browns priority is to:</p>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div class="nner_text_container full_width top_margin"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/health.png" alt="health" width="1001" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-539" /></div>     \r\n      <div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin ">\r\n        <ul>\r\n          <li>Stem the tide of dangerous drugs into our community and cut our property crime rate by continuing to accelerate our narcotics investigations and community policing efforts and by leveraging technology as a force multiplier.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div class="community_btmPart full_width ">\r\n        <div class="inner_text_container full_width ">\r\n          <h2>Healthy Community</h2>\r\n          <p class="top_padding" ><span class="blue_color1">Goal:</span> Radically improve the health and wellness of our residents through healthy behaviors, healthy lifestyles and access to healthcare.</p>\r\n          <p class="top_padding" >Obesity, substance abuse and mental illness remain the most vexing health problems facing us today.  Were making great progress on these fronts but we have much more work to do.</p>\r\n          <p class="top_padding btm_padding1" >Mayor Kristen Browns plan ensures that the community collectively supports both mental and physical wellness. </p>\r\n          <ul>\r\n            <li>Cut the demand for drugs in our community through significantly greater leadership and resources directed toward prevention and treatment of substance abuse and mental health disorders.  Cutting the supply of drugs will remain a tremendous challenge until we seriously address the demand for drugs in our community.</li>\r\n            <li>Build People Bridges, dedicated bike and pedestrian bridges, to make important and safe People Trail connections over our rivers, busy streets and railroad tracks, including the riverfront of the Pump House property, over Lindsey into downtown at the 3rd Street Bridge and over Haw Creek and Central near 3rd Street. </li>\r\n            <li>Form a public-private partnership to develop an indoor athletic training facility on the airports property for use by our local sports teams, including soccer, football and other field sports teams.</li>            \r\n          </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>', 'Advance the Safety and Health of Our Community', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '297-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-14 05:34:28', '2015-01-14 05:34:28', '', 297, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/297-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(560, 1, '2015-01-14 05:37:21', '2015-01-14 05:37:21', '  <div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n        <h1 class="red_color ">Advance Economic Prosperity and Well-Paying Jobs</h1>\r\n        <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div class="jobs_container">\r\n        <div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n          <p class="top_margin"> Economic prosperity is another key driver of our quality of life because it increases wealth and living standards both collectively and individually.  Our exceptional economic statistics speak volumes about the relative strength of our economy and our business-friendly  climate. However, there is still much work to be done to sustain a   growing economy of well-paying jobs.</p>\r\n              <p class="btm_padding1 top_margin">Mayor Kristen Browns plan continues and builds upon a very pro-growth environment by ensuring businesses have access to the resources they need to thrive and create well-paying jobs.  Those resources include a skilled workforce, available land and infrastructure and cultural and recreational amenities that attract and retain a skilled workforce. </p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class="inner_text_container full_width"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/paynig_job2.png" alt="paynig_job" width="1001" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-542" /></div>       \r\n      <div class="community_btmPart full_width ">\r\n        <div class="inner_text_container full_width ">\r\n          <h2>Work-Ready Community</h2>\r\n          <p class="top_padding"<span class="blue_color1">Goal:</span> Close the skills gap so our employers are competitive and prosper and our employees have the skills to fill high-wage, high-demand jobs.</p>\r\n          <p class="top_padding btm_padding1">The availability of skilled workers is the single most important factor in our economic growth.  However, the skills our employers require today have outpaced the skills of our workforce.  Our mandate is to produce a ready pipeline of skilled and job-ready workers.  Mayor Browns plan will significantly help close the skills gap.</p>\r\n          <ul>\r\n            <li>Invest TIF dollars to fund custom job training programs that prepare our local workforce for our employers in-demand skilled jobs. </li>\r\n          </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div class="community_btmPart full_width ">\r\n        <div class="inner_text_container full_width ">\r\n          <h2>Business-Friendly Community</h2>\r\n          <p class="top_padding btm_padding1">Goal: Provide the environment and resources that ensure our employers prosper and create good jobs consistent with our values.</p>\r\n          <ul>\r\n            <li>Redevelop the 700 acres at the old Walesboro airport into the Walesboro Industrial Park, ensuring shovel-ready land for industrial growth.</li>\r\n          </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div class="community_btmPart full_width ">\r\n        <div class="inner_text_container full_width ">\r\n          <h2>Cultural and Creative Capital</h2>\r\n          <p class="top_padding btm_padding1"><span class="blue_color1">Goal:</span> Increase cultural and recreational amenities and downtown multi-family housing to attract and retain talent. </p>\r\n          <ul>\r\n            <li>Encourage private redevelopment of key properties in the Arts District in keeping with the Arts District Strategic Plan, including the Sears property, the redevelopment properties at 2nd and Lafayette, 6th and Washington and the Pump House. </li>\r\n            <li>Redevelopment of the Mill Race Park Amphitheater into a flood-resistant, modern and versatile outdoor performing arts facility for both community events and touring acts. </li>\r\n          </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>', 'Advance Economic Prosperity and Well-Paying Jobs', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '299-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-14 05:37:21', '2015-01-14 05:37:21', '', 299, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/299-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
