(587, 1, '2015-01-14 08:01:55', '2015-01-14 08:01:55', '<div class="main_heading full_width top_margin">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Restored and Improved Our Parks and Community Facilities</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="blue_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n  <div class="inner_blue_container">\r\n    <p class="btm_padding1">We have an outstanding parks system that provides fun-filled, healthy experiences and lifetime memories for our kids and families.</p>\r\n  <p class="btm_padding1">Unfortunately, capital maintenance and repairs to our parks and community facilities had been deferred for many years, leading to significant facilities deterioration, and in some cases, non-functional and unsafe conditions.  Community treasures, Hamilton and Donner Centers, were particularly dilapidated and one the verge of being safety hazards.  Some neighborhood parks were badly neglected and had become havens for drug users.</p>\r\n  <p class="btm_padding1">Mayor Kristen Brown strongly believes that our parks and community facilities are indispensable and cherished community resources that must be safe, inviting and well-maintained outdoor and indoor spaces. </p>  </div>\r\n  <div class="img_container"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/parks1.png" alt="parks" width="370" height="498" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-440" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Embarked on an aggressive program to invest $5.5 million - $3.9 million of public money and $1.7 million of private donations - to preserve and improve our existing parks and community facilities, including Hamilton and Donner Centers. </li>\r\n<li>Reversed years of neglect and deterioration of our communitys most cherished facilities and ensured they are safe and inviting outdoor and indoor spaces enjoyed by todays and future generations.  </li>\r\n\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Parks', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '168-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-14 08:01:55', '2015-01-14 08:01:55', '', 168, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/168-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(588, 1, '2015-01-14 08:03:05', '2015-01-14 08:03:05', '<div class="main_heading full_width top_margin">\r\n  <h1>Made Columbus Safer, Protected You and Your Family  </h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n  <div class="inner_blue_container">\r\n    <p class="btm_padding1">Along with maintaining and improving our public infrastructure, public safety is job number one for Mayor Kristen Brown. </p>\r\n<h2 >Accelerated Law Enforcement Efforts</h2>\r\n<p class="btm_padding1">Under Mayor Browns leadership, we have more police officers on our streets than at any time in our citys history and never before have they been more productive. </p>    \r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="img_container"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/safety1.png" alt="safety" width="609" height="307" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-549" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Choked the flow of dangerous drugs into our community by cracking down on a threefold increase in the number of dealers of methamphetamine and heroin. .</li>\r\n<li>Restored stability to our hardest-hit neighborhoods with a 45% increase in community policing patrols and a new dedicated community policing unit.  </li>\r\n<li>Cut violent crime nearly in half and cut property crime by 23%.Reduced the number of traffic accidents through an acceleration of traffic enforcement efforts.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2>Improved Emergency Medical Services and Saved Tax Dollars</h2>\r\n<p>Mayor Kristen Brown and her team have significantly advanced emergency medical services, ensuring residents have the best chance for surviving a life-threatening event. </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Awarded a new ambulance contract to Columbus Regional Hospital after conducting a fair, transparent and competitive bidding process resulting in significantly improved service and reduced costs to taxpayers from nearly $1 million every year to $0 a year.</li>\r\n<li>Increased the number of paramedic firefighters certified in advanced life-support techniques to staff one on all six engines at every fire station every day.  </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2>Improved Rescue, Disaster and Extreme Weather Response</h2>\r\n<p>Mayor Kristen Brown and her team have ensured that we are well prepared for the myriad of threats our community faces.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Sold the mayors city-owned vehicle to fund ice water rescue equipment for City firefighters to ensure optimal victim survivability around the citys 161 ponds and lakes.</li>\r\n<li>Unveiled the first-ever Flood Risk Warning and Management Plan on the fifth anniversary of the 2008 flood. Never again will we be unprepared.</li>\r\n<li>Deployed an emergency notification system that sends alerts to citizens by voicemail, text messages and emails during emergencies. </li>\r\n<li>Ensured that our roads were cleared of snow and ice and potholes were patched in a timely manner during extreme winter weather the last two years.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Public Safety', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '170-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-14 08:03:05', '2015-01-14 08:03:05', '', 170, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/170-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(589, 1, '2015-01-14 08:04:00', '2015-01-14 08:04:00', '<div class="main_heading full_width top_margin">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Revitalized and Strengthened Our Neighborhoods </h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<p class="top_margin">Mayor Kristen Brown has taken a comprehensive approach to revitalization and made tremendous progress making our more challenged neighborhoods safer, prouder and free of blight.  </p>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n<img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Neighborhoods.png" alt="Neighborhoods" width="988" height="496" /></div>\r\n<ul class="top_padding">\r\n<li>Substantially improved conditions in our neighborhoods through regular neighborhood meetings, community policing, cleanup projects, and code enforcement.</li>\r\n<li>Turned 9th Street Neighborhood Park into a safe and inviting place for kids to play from what it had become: a magnet for anti-social behavior and criminal activity, particularly drug-related issues. </li>\r\n<li>Ordered the demolishment or repair of twenty-three abandoned, blighted and unsafe homes and commercial buildings.</li>\r\n<li>Begun the Citys first ever Blight Elimination Program with a $760,000 grant to fund the demolishment of approximately three dozen abandoned and blighted houses.</li>\r\n<li>Completed the State Street Revitalization Plan to redevelop State Street and revitalize the surrounding neighborhoods. Mayor Brown voted in favor of funding and implementing the first phase of the State Street Plan this year.</li>\r\n<li>Partnered with two private developers who are planning to remediate and redevelop the Golden Castings Foundry site, a decade-long source of blight in the heart of our city.  The redevelopment will provide much-needed addition high-quality, affordable housing and an assisted living facility.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Neighborhoods', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '172-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-14 08:04:00', '2015-01-14 08:04:00', '', 172, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/172-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(590, 1, '2015-01-14 08:04:32', '2015-01-14 08:04:32', '<div class="main_heading full_width top_margin">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Encouraged Job Growth </h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<p class="top_margin">\r\n Under Mayor Kristen Browns leadership, Columbus has set records for the number of jobs and employment.  The Columbus metropolitan area is at all-time record highs for both the number of jobs in our community  more than 51,000 - and the number of residents who are employed  more than 41,000.   Our unemployment rate is currently the second lowest in the state.</p> \r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="inner_text_container full_width btm_padding1 "><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/jobs1.png" alt="jobs" width="1001" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-535" /></div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>2,500 more jobs were created and nearly 3,500 more residents are employed in our community than three years ago. </li>\r\n<li>Our largest employer, Cummins Inc., announced they would begin engine production at the Columbus Engine Plant again and add another 500 well-paying jobs to our community.  Cummins announcement was a resounding reaffirmation of Cummins strong commitment to Columbus, Indiana.</li>\r\n<li>Provided tax incentives, encouraging the creation and retention of more than another 600 jobs and investmentsexceeding $250 million.  </li>\r\n<li>Developed a preliminary plan to redevelop the nearly 700 acres of the former Walesboro Airport into an industrial park to provide shovel-ready industrial sites for continued job-creating growth.</li>\r\n<li>Developed the citys first Strategic Growth Plan to readily and efficiently accommodate the citys growth outside todays city limits.</li>\r\n<li>Formed a public-private partnership to develop a 114-bed, $5 million student housing complex at the airport.  This is the game-changer for our four colleges recruitment efforts and our ability to produce a steady pipeline of skilled and educated workers that our employers need to prosper.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n', 'Jobs', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '174-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-14 08:04:32', '2015-01-14 08:04:32', '', 174, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/174-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(591, 1, '2015-01-14 08:05:19', '2015-01-14 08:05:19', '<div class="main_heading full_width top_margin">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Ushered in a New Era of Good Government </h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin"> \r\n    <p>Mayor Kristen Brown believes that how government operates is every bit as important as what it accomplishes.  Her goal is to be the most honest, transparent, inclusive, responsive and accountable municipal government of our size.  And she and her team are delivering.   </p>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin btm_padding1"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/government1.png" alt="government" width="1001" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-530" /></div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width ">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Dissolved the Citys private corporation, Columbus Downtown Inc., and stopped spending taxpayer money behind closed doors. </li>\r\n<li>Dramatically improved city governments transparency with live and on-demand broadcasting of public meetings online. This service has attracted thousands of views.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Gained adoption of a comprehensive code of ethical conduct, helping assure you that public officials and employees are operating in your best interest  not in their own personal interests or in favor of special interests.  </li>\r\n<li>Attained accreditation for the police department, ensuring our officers maintain the highest professional standards and operate with the utmost integrity, transparency and accountability.  Only three percent of the law enforcement agencies in the nation achieve this status. </li>\r\n<li>Improved service by launching uReport, an online customer service request application that gives you the opportunity to quickly and easily request city services. </li>\r\n<li>Developed a long-term strategic plan for city government with priorities and measurable objectives and published annual reports detailing results.</li>\r\n<li>Achieved a finding-free audit from the Indiana State Board of Accounts in 2013.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Good Government', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '176-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-14 08:05:19', '2015-01-14 08:05:19', '', 176, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/176-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(592, 1, '2015-01-14 08:05:52', '2015-01-14 08:05:52', '<div class="main_heading full_width top_margin">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Made Tough Calls to Get Our Fiscal House in Order and Lower Taxes </h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="blue_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n  <div class="inner_blue_container">\r\n    <p class="btm_padding">Mayor Kristen Brown understands she works for the taxpayers who write the checks to local government, not for the special interests who cash the checks. </p>\r\n    <p class="btm_padding">Mayor Brown has been shaping city governments organization and budget to lower taxes and fees, best advance your priorities and ensure city government gets the most for your dollar.  This has resulted in changes in the way city government does business and a more streamlined, priority-driven budget. </p>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="img_container"><a href="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/a-record-of-sucess-Fiscal-Responsibility1.png"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/a-record-of-sucess-Fiscal-Responsibility1.png" alt="a-record-of-sucess-Fiscal-Responsibility" width="495" height="349" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-250" /></a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n<h2>Eliminated Mandatory Fees and Championed a Decrease in Property Taxes</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Repealed the mandatory trash fees from residents utility bills, returning $1.4 million a year to our citizens.</li>\r\n<li>Voted to return $3 million of TIF property tax revenues to the taxpayers to reduce property tax rates.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2>Changed Spending Priorities</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Terminated the expensive and problematic outdoor sports complex.</li>\r\n<li>Invested in repairing and restoring existing infrastructure, roads and public parks and community facilities, not developing new facilities.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2>Saved Taxpayers Money</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Conducted competitive purchasing processes for services and consolidated purchasing of supplies and equipment, saving taxpayers more than a million dollars a year.  </li>\r\n<li>Saved more than $500,000 annually by decreasing taxpayers share of rising employee health care costs.</li>\r\n<li>Terminated the personal use of city vehicles except for police and fire.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2>Maintained Financial Strength</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Issued no incremental new debt and maintained healthy cash reserves.</li>\r\n<li>Maintained Standard and Poors very strong credit rating of a AA-.\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Fiscal Responsibility', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '178-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-14 08:05:52', '2015-01-14 08:05:52', '', 178, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/178-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(593, 1, '2015-01-14 08:06:24', '2015-01-14 08:06:24', '<div class="main_heading full_width top_margin top_margin">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Met Demand for Expanded Services With No Additional Tax Burden</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<p class="top_margin">Mayor Kristen Brown has met the communitys demand for expanded City services with no increase in taxes and after eliminating the mandatory trash fees.</p>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Services1.png" alt="Services" width="1002" height="382" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-442" /></div>\r\n<ul class="top_padding">\r\n<li>Curbside Recycling - Formed a public-private partnership enabling the City to provide a curbside recycling service for residents for no additional fees and free 96 gallon toters for single-stream collection, no sorting required.</li>\r\n<li>Animal Care Services Achieved a 100-percent adoption rate for healthy dogs for the last three years.  Animal Care Services has for the first time found all dogs loving, permanent homes, eliminating the need for euthanasia due to space constraints at our shelter.  Adoptions of both dogs and cats are at all-time highs. </li>\r\n<li>Transit Service  Will soon add a fifth transit route to include service to and from the west side on SR 46 and expanded week-day hours of all routes to 8 pm.  These changes were the first and second most requested service improvements by transit customers.</li>\r\n<li>School Resource Officers - In partnership with the school system, dedicated two police officers in the schools to improve our kids safety and to encourage children and teens to avoid drugs, bullying and violence.</li>\r\n<li>Began cost-sharing program with homeowners to repair sidewalks and curbs.</li>\r\n<li>Shared Cost Sidewalk and Curb Program  Introduced the Shared Cost Sidewalk and Curb Program, a cost-sharing program for homeowners to address overdue repairs to sidewalks and curbs.  The program offers outstanding value to homeowners and increases the safety and appearances of our neighborhoods. </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Expanded Services', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '180-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-14 08:06:24', '2015-01-14 08:06:24', '', 180, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/180-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(594, 1, '2015-01-14 08:09:19', '2015-01-14 08:09:19', '<div class="main_heading full_width top_margin">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Repaired and Rebuilt Our Roads </h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n    <p class="btm_padding1">For years, Columbus underinvested in maintaining its roads.  When Mayor Kristen Brown assumed office, we were far behind schedule and many of our streets were in total disrepair, creating difficult and unsafe driving conditions and wear and tear on our vehicles.</p><p>Mayor Brown made our most critical infrastructure a top priority.</p>    \r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="inner_text_container full_width"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/roads2.png" alt="roads" width="1001" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-544" /></div>\r\n\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Completed the largest road repair project in the citys history, investing nearly $10 million in three years to reconstruct and resurface approximately 40 miles of crumbling streets.  By comparison the City was spending less than $400,000 repaving only about 4 miles of roads a year prior to her assuming the job of mayor in 2012. </li>\r\n<li>Completed construction or begun the design of <span class="li_blue_color"><a href="">six major road improvement projects</a></span> for a combined investment of more than $20 million funded primarily by federal transportation dollars.</li>\r\n<li>Fourth Street  this $2.2 million in 2012 project transformed 4th Street from Jackson to Lafayette.  Its now pedestrian friendly, accommodates expanded outdoor seating and is readily closed to traffic for community events and celebrations. </li>\r\n<li>200S  this $3 million project in 2013 alleviated traffic congestion and made this old country road, now a suburban collector, significantly safer for motorists, school buses and pedestrians by widening the lanes, adding a left-turn lane, a storm sewer system, a sidewalk and railroad crossing improvements.</li>\r\n<li>Carr Hill Road  this $2.2 million in 2014 project transformed this former country road into a suburban collector to better serve the growing residential area on the west side of Columbus. The improved street provide wider traffic lanes, curbs, gutters, storm sewers, bicycle lanes and sidewalks on both sides of the street.</li>\r\n<li>Indiana Avenue  this $6.2 million project in 2015 will improve this suburban collector serving Columbus East High School and connecting two arterials, Marr Road and State Street, on Columbus east side.  Lanes will be widened and a storm sewer system, bicycle lanes and sidewalks will be added.  Currently the utility relocation is complete and construction will be completed this year.</li>\r\n<li>Rocky Ford Taylor to Talley  this $7 million project will transform this old country road into a suburban collector.  It includes widened lanes in each direction, a two-way left turn lane, bicycle lanes, a storm sewer system and sidewalks on both sides of the street. The City is currently acquiring right-of-way for this project and construction is planned in 2016.</li>\r\n<li>Maple Street  this $1 million project will extend Maple Street from Tipton Lane to U.S. 31, giving pedestrians, bicyclists and motorists significantly safer routes and alleviating traffic congestion to and from school in the four-school campus area that includes Columbus North High School, Northside Middle School, Schmitt Elementary School and St. Bartholomew Catholic School. The City is currently in the design engineering phase of this project and construction is planned in 2016.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Roads', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '166-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-14 08:09:19', '2015-01-14 08:09:19', '', 166, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/166-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(595, 1, '2015-01-14 08:14:53', '2015-01-14 08:14:53', '<div class="main_heading full_width top_margin">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Encouraged Job Growth </h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<p class="top_margin">\r\n Under Mayor Kristen Browns leadership, Columbus has set records for the number of jobs and employment.  The Columbus metropolitan area is at all-time record highs for both the number of jobs in our community  more than 51,000 - and the number of residents who are employed  more than 41,000.   Our unemployment rate is currently the second lowest in the state.</p> \r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="inner_text_container full_width btm_padding1 "><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/jobs1.png" alt="jobs" width="1001" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-535" /></div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>2,500 more jobs were created and nearly 3,500 more residents are employed in our community than three years ago. </li>\r\n<li>Our largest employer, Cummins Inc., announced they would begin engine production at the Columbus Engine Plant again and add another 500 well-paying jobs to our community.  Cummins announcement was a resounding reaffirmation of Cummins strong commitment to Columbus, Indiana.</li>\r\n<li>Provided tax incentives, encouraging the creation and retention of more than another <span class="li_red_color">600 jobs and investments ex</span>ceeding $250 million.  </li>\r\n<li>Developed a preliminary plan to redevelop the nearly <span class="li_red_color">700 acres</span> of the former Walesboro Airport into an industrial park to provide shovel-ready industrial sites for continued job-creating growth.</li>\r\n<li>Developed the citys first Strategic Growth Plan to readily and efficiently accommodate the citys growth outside todays city limits.</li>\r\n<li>Formed a public-private partnership to develop a 114-bed, $5 million student housing complex at the airport.  This is the game-changer for our four colleges recruitment efforts and our ability to produce a steady pipeline of skilled and educated workers that our employers need to prosper.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n', 'Jobs', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '174-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-14 08:14:53', '2015-01-14 08:14:53', '', 174, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/174-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(596, 1, '2015-01-14 08:27:27', '2015-01-14 08:27:27', '<div class="main_heading full_width ">\r\n<h1 class="red_color ">A Plan for the Future: Advance Columbus</h1>\r\n<div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="plan_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n<div class="inner_blue_container">\r\n<p class="btm_padding">Our community is a special and remarkable combination of people and place. World-renown architecture is woven into the fabric of our daily lives. We benefit from exciting cultural and recreational amenities, a diverse population, a strong sense of community and teamwork and a commitment to excellence.</p>\r\nOur local economy is a powerhouse relative to the rest of the state and nation. The number of jobs in our community is at an all-time high. The number of residents employed is also at an all-time high.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="plan_rightPart"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/plan3.png" alt="plan" width="438" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-554" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="plan_inner_part full_width">\r\n<p class="btm_padding top_margin">By every major measure, our quality of life in Columbus, Indiana is far better than the state and even the nation as a whole.\r\nBut we are Columbus. We aim even higher and we have an unshakable confidence in our ability to create an even more remarkable future.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="red_color btm_padding1">OUR VISION</h2>\r\n<p class="btm_padding">Our vision is <strong>to be the very best community of its size in the country. </strong> It is a bold and ambitious vision.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="blue_color btm_padding1 ">ONE CITY. ONE PLAN. ADVANCE COLUMBUS.</h2>\r\n<p class="btm_padding1">In order to advance Columbus toward this future, Mayor Kristen Brown partnered with the leaders of several other public and private organizations dedicated to serving our community. Together with much public engagement, they created Advance Columbus, a roadmap to solve our toughest challenges, leverage our greatest strengths and capitalize on our many opportunities to advance our quality of life for today and for future generations.</p>\r\n<p class="btm_padding1">Mayor Kristen Brown rolled out Advance Columbus at her State of the City address in 2013.</p>\r\n<p class="btm_padding1">She also made it the City of Columbus mission to do its part in advancing Columbus toward the future we envision. Last year, Mayor Brown and department heads developed the City governments first strategic plan, aligning the city governments priorities with the communitys highest priorities as defined by Advance Columbus.</p>\r\n<p class="btm_padding1 blue_color_normal">The plans priorities are to:</p>\r\n<p class="btm_padding1">1. Advance Quality Infrastructure\r\n\r\n2. Advance Economic Prosperity and Well-Paying Jobs\r\n\r\n3. Advance the Safety and Health of Our Community</p>\r\n<p class="btm_padding1">Recognizing that how we get there is every bit as important as getting there, Mayor Browns plan importantly includes advancing Columbus in a way that is consistent with the <a>values of good government.</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>', 'A Plan for the Future', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '12-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-14 08:27:27', '2015-01-14 08:27:27', '', 12, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/12-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(597, 1, '2015-01-14 08:28:26', '2015-01-14 08:28:26', '<div class="main_heading full_width top_margin">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Restored and Improved Our Parks and Community Facilities</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="blue_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n  <div class="inner_blue_container">\r\n    <p class="btm_padding1">We have an outstanding parks system that provides fun-filled, healthy experiences and lifetime memories for our kids and families.</p>\r\n  <p class="btm_padding1">Unfortunately, capital maintenance and repairs to our parks and community facilities had been deferred for many years, leading to significant facilities deterioration, and in some cases, non-functional and unsafe conditions.  Community treasures, Hamilton and Donner Centers, were particularly dilapidated and one the verge of being safety hazards.  Some neighborhood parks were badly neglected and had become havens for drug users.</p>\r\n  <p class="btm_padding1">Mayor Kristen Brown strongly believes that our parks and community facilities are indispensable and cherished community resources that must be safe, inviting and well-maintained outdoor and indoor spaces. </p>  </div>\r\n  <div class="img_container"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/parks1.png" alt="parks" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-440" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Embarked on an aggressive program to invest $5.5 million - $3.9 million of public money and $1.7 million of private donations - to preserve and improve our existing parks and community facilities, including Hamilton and Donner Centers. </li>\r\n<li>Reversed years of neglect and deterioration of our communitys most cherished facilities and ensured they are safe and inviting outdoor and indoor spaces enjoyed by todays and future generations.  </li>\r\n\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Parks', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '168-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-14 08:28:26', '2015-01-14 08:28:26', '', 168, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/168-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
