ers from nearly $1 million every year to $0 a year.</li>\r\n<li>Increased the number of paramedic firefighters certified in advanced life-support techniques to staff one on all six engines at every fire station every day.  </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2>Improved Rescue, Disaster and Extreme Weather Response</h2>\r\n<p>Mayor Kristen Brown and her team have ensured that we are well prepared for the myriad of threats our community faces.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Sold the mayors city-owned vehicle to fund ice water rescue equipment for City firefighters to ensure optimal victim survivability around the citys 161 ponds and lakes.</li>\r\n<li>Unveiled the first-ever Flood Risk Warning and Management Plan on the fifth anniversary of the 2008 flood. Never again will we be unprepared.</li>\r\n<li>Deployed an emergency notification system that sends alerts to citizens by voicemail, text messages and emails during emergencies. </li>\r\n<li>Ensured that our roads were cleared of snow and ice and potholes were patched in a timely manner during extreme winter weather the last two years.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Public Safety', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '170-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-14 09:11:48', '2015-01-14 09:11:48', '', 170, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/170-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
