(664, 1, '2015-01-15 01:38:22', '2015-01-15 01:38:22', '<div class="main_heading full_width top_margin">\r\n<h1>Made Columbus Safer, Protected You and Your Family</h1>\r\n<div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n<p class="btm_padding">Along with maintaining and improving our public infrastructure, public safety is job number one for Mayor Kristen Brown.</p>\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-613" src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/safety2.png" alt="safety" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Accelerated Law Enforcement Efforts</h2>\r\nUnder Mayor Browns leadership, we have more police officers on our streets than at any time in our citys history and never before have they been more productive.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Choked the flow of dangerous drugs into our community by cracking down on a threefold increase in the number of dealers of methamphetamine and heroin.</li>\r\n	<li>Restored stability to our hardest-hit neighborhoods with a 45% increase in community policing patrols and a new dedicated community policing unit.</li>\r\n	<li>Cut violent crime nearly in half and cut property crime by 23%. Reduced the number of traffic accidents through an acceleration of traffic enforcement efforts.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2>Improved Emergency Medical Services and Saved Tax Dollars</h2>\r\nMayor Kristen Brown and her team have significantly advanced emergency medical services, ensuring residents have the best chance for surviving a life-threatening event.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Awarded a new ambulance contract to Columbus Regional Hospital after conducting a fair, transparent and competitive bidding process resulting in significantly improved service and reduced costs to taxpayers from nearly $1 million every year to $0 a year.</li>\r\n	<li>Increased the number of paramedic firefighters certified in advanced life-support techniques to staff one on all six engines at every fire station every day.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2>Improved Rescue, Disaster and Extreme Weather Response</h2>\r\nMayor Kristen Brown and her team have ensured that we are well prepared for the myriad of threats our community faces.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Sold the mayors city-owned vehicle to fund ice water rescue equipment for City firefighters to ensure optimal victim survivability around the citys 161 ponds and lakes.</li>\r\n	<li>Unveiled the first-ever Flood Risk Warning and Management Plan on the fifth anniversary of the 2008 flood. Never again will we be unprepared.</li>\r\n	<li>Deployed an emergency notification system that sends alerts to citizens by voicemail, text messages and emails during emergencies.</li>\r\n	<li>Ensured that our roads were cleared of snow and ice and potholes were patched in a timely manner during extreme winter weather the last two years.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Public Safety', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '170-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-15 01:38:22', '2015-01-15 01:38:22', '', 170, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/170-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(665, 1, '2015-01-15 01:40:57', '2015-01-15 01:40:57', '<div class="main_heading full_width top_margin">\r\n<h1 class="red_color ">Encouraged Job Growth</h1>\r\n<div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<p class="top_margin">Under Mayor Kristen Browns leadership, Columbus has set records for the number of jobs and employment. The Columbus metropolitan area is at all-time record highs for both the number of jobs in our community  more than 51,000 - and the number of residents who are employed  more than 41,000. Our unemployment rate is currently the second lowest in the state.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width btm_padding1 "><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-535" src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/jobs1.png" alt="jobs" width="1001" height="320" /></div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>2,500 more jobs were created and nearly 3,500 more residents are employed in our community than three years ago.</li>\r\n	<li>Our largest employer, Cummins Inc., announced they would begin engine production at the Columbus Engine Plant again and add another 500 well-paying jobs to our community. Cummins announcement was a resounding reaffirmation of Cummins strong commitment to Columbus, Indiana.</li>\r\n	<li>Provided tax incentives, encouraging the creation and retention of more than another 600 jobs and investments exceeding $250 million.</li>\r\n	<li>Developed a preliminary plan to redevelop the nearly 700 acres of the former Walesboro Airport into an industrial park to provide shovel-ready industrial sites for continued job-creating growth.</li>\r\n	<li>Developed the citys first Strategic Growth Plan to readily and efficiently accommodate the citys growth outside todays city limits.</li>\r\n	<li>Formed a public-private partnership to develop a 114-bed, $5 million student housing complex at the airport. This is the game-changer for our four colleges recruitment efforts and our ability to produce a steady pipeline of skilled and educated workers that our employers need to prosper.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Jobs', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '174-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-15 01:40:57', '2015-01-15 01:40:57', '', 174, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/174-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(666, 1, '2015-01-15 01:43:52', '2015-01-15 01:43:52', '  <div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n        <h1 class="red_color ">Advance Economic Prosperity and Well-Paying Jobs</h1>\r\n        <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div class="jobs_container">\r\n        <div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n          <p class="top_margin"> Economic prosperity is another key driver of our quality of life because it increases wealth and living standards both collectively and individually.  Our exceptional economic statistics speak volumes about the relative strength of our economy and our business-friendly  climate. However, there is still much work to be done to sustain a   growing economy of well-paying jobs.</p>\r\n              <p class="btm_padding1 top_margin">Mayor Kristen Browns plan continues and builds upon a very pro-growth environment by ensuring businesses have access to the resources they need to thrive and create well-paying jobs.  Those resources include a skilled workforce, available land and infrastructure and cultural and recreational amenities that attract and retain a skilled workforce. </p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class="inner_text_container full_width"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/paynig_job2.png" alt="paynig_job" width="1001" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-542" /></div>       \r\n      <div class="community_btmPart full_width ">\r\n        <div class="inner_text_container full_width ">\r\n          <h2>Work-Ready Community</h2>\r\n          <p class="top_padding"><span class="blue_color1">Goal:</span> Close the skills gap so our employers are competitive and prosper and our employees have the skills to fill high-wage, high-demand jobs.</p>\r\n          <p class="top_padding btm_padding1">The availability of skilled workers is the single most important factor in our economic growth.  However, the skills our employers require today have outpaced the skills of our workforce.  Our mandate is to produce a ready pipeline of skilled and job-ready workers.  Mayor Browns plan will significantly help close the skills gap.</p>\r\n          <ul>\r\n            <li>Invest TIF dollars to fund custom job training programs that prepare our local workforce for our employers in-demand skilled jobs. </li>\r\n          </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div class="community_btmPart full_width ">\r\n        <div class="inner_text_container full_width ">\r\n          <h2>Business-Friendly Community</h2>\r\n          <p class="top_padding btm_padding1"><span class="blue_color1">Goal:</span> Provide the environment and resources that ensure our employers prosper and create good jobs consistent with our values.</p>\r\n          <ul>\r\n            <li>Redevelop the 700 acres at the old Walesboro airport into the Walesboro Industrial Park, ensuring shovel-ready land for industrial growth.</li>\r\n          </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div class="community_btmPart full_width ">\r\n        <div class="inner_text_container full_width ">\r\n          <h2>Cultural and Creative Capital</h2>\r\n          <p class="top_padding btm_padding1"><span class="blue_color1">Goal:</span> Increase cultural and recreational amenities and downtown multi-family housing to attract and retain talent. </p>\r\n          <ul>\r\n            <li>Encourage private redevelopment of key properties in the Arts District in keeping with the Arts District Strategic Plan, including the Sears property, the redevelopment properties at 2nd and Lafayette, 6th and Washington and the Pump House. </li>\r\n            <li>Redevelopment of the Mill Race Park Amphitheater into a flood-resistant, modern and versatile outdoor performing arts facility for both community events and touring acts. </li>\r\n          </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>', 'Advance Economic Prosperity and Well-Paying Jobs', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '299-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-15 01:43:52', '2015-01-15 01:43:52', '', 299, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/299-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
